mn--default--12">
                     <p></p>
                     <h2 id=3D"getting-to-a-healthy-weight">Getting to a he=
althy weight</h2>
                     <p><strong>To maintain a healthy weight</strong>, you =
need to balance the number of calories you take in with the number you use =
consistently over time. Even if you take in more calories than usual one da=
y, you can still maintain your weight if you reduce your calorie intake or =
burn more calories than usual another day.</p>
                     <p>To stay at a healthy weight, you can:</p>
                     <ul>
                      <li>Focus on eating a <a href=3D"https://www.cancer.o=
rg/cancer/risk-prevention/diet-physical-activity/eat-healthy.html">healthy =
diet</a>.</li>
                      <li>Be <a href=3D"https://www.cancer.org/cancer/risk-=
prevention/diet-physical-activity/get-active.html">active</a>.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p><strong>If you have <a href=3D"https://www.cancer.o=
rg/cancer/risk-prevention/diet-physical-activity/body-weight-and-cancer-ris=
k.html">excess weight</a> and want to lose weight</strong>, the best way to=
 get to a healthy weight is to limit the calories you take in and burn more=
 calories through physical activity.&nbsp;</p>
                     <p>To get to a healthy weight, you can:</p>
                     <ul>
                      <li>Focus on eating a <a href=3D"https://www.cancer.o=
rg/cancer/risk-prevention/diet-physical-activity/eat-healthy.html">healthy =
diet</a></li>
                      <li>Be <a href=3D"https://www.cancer.org/cancer/risk-=
prevention/diet-physical-activity/get-active.html">active</a></li>
                      <li>Reduce your daily calories by 500 through diet, e=
xercise, or both. Or you can reduce your total weekly calories.</li>
                      <li>Aim to lose 1-2 pounds per week.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>A plan to get to and stay at a healthy weight will =
be different for everyone. You should always work with your health care tea=
m to develop a specific plan for you.</p>
                     <h2 id=3D"more-interactive-tools">More interactive too=
ls</h2>
                     <p>&nbsp;Use our other interactive tools to stay healt=
hy:</p>
                     <p></p>
